---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — Mangesh Bide" description="Software engineer working on backend systems and infrastructure.">
  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 pt-16 pb-16">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-8">About</h1>

    <div class="prose dark:prose-invert">
      <p>
        I'm Mangesh — a software engineer from India. Currently at Houseworks Technologies
        building healthcare APIs in Python and Django. I spend most of my time writing
        backend code, thinking about data models, and arguing with myself about whether a
        migration is safe.
      </p>

      <p>
        Before this job I taught myself to program because I wanted to know how video games
        worked, then took a CS degree to patch the holes. Since then I've shipped multi-tenant
        SaaS, small ML models, React frontends, and a lot of glue code in between.
        The most useful thing I've learned is that code someone else can maintain matters
        more than code that's clever.
      </p>

      <p>
        These days I work across Python, Django, DRF, Terraform, and AWS. I'm comfortable
        in React and TypeScript when I have to be. I write here because explaining something
        is the fastest way I've found to notice I didn't actually understand it.
      </p>

      <p>
        A full résumé is at <a href="/Resume.pdf">Resume.pdf</a>. Email is in the footer.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
